<dl id="n12196e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12196e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12196e"> 196(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> voice of Esau <small>Green</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n12196e"><li>FW 487.21f </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/lexrA.htm#n12196e">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/l39rA.htm#n12196e">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n12196e">MS BL 47484a-42</ms> </li><li>JJA 58:177 <a name="rAd4" href="../../FF/fdra/rda.htm#rAd4">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/rA/rAd4.htm#n12196e">Draft: III&sect;3A.4</a> </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: See Genesis 27:22. By bringing him a dish of venison, Jacob gets his father Isaac&apos;s blessing, intended for his older brother Esau. On the advice of his mother he covers his hands with goatskin to make them feel like Esau&apos;s hairy hands. The suspicious Isaac remarks: &ldquo;The voice is Jacob&apos;s voice, but the hands are the hands of Esau.&apos;&rdquo; </mm> </dd></dl>
